verses.text_plain: I will praise thee, O Lord, with my whole heart; I will shew forth all thy marvellous works.
verses.verse_html: 1I will praise thee, O Lord, with my whole heart; I will shew forth all thy marvellous works.

verses.text_plain: I will be glad and rejoice in thee: I will sing praise to thy name, O thou most High.
verses.verse_html: 2I will be glad and rejoice in thee: I will sing praise to thy name, O thou most High.

tokens.text: in thee: I will sing praise

verses.text_plain: When mine enemies are turned back, they shall fall and perish at thy presence.
verses.verse_html: 3When mine enemies are turned back, they shall fall and perish at thy presence.

verses.text_plain: For thou hast maintained my right and my cause; thou satest in the throne judging right.
verses.verse_html:
4For thou hast maintained my right and my cause; thou satest in the throne judging right. ▼
▼ maintained…: Heb. made my judgment
 , ▼
▼ judging right: Heb. judging in righteousness

footnotes.body_html: ▼ maintained…: Heb. made my judgment

footnotes.body_text: ▼ judging right: Heb. judging in righteousness
footnotes.body_html: ▼ judging right: Heb. judging in righteousness

verses.text_plain: Thou hast rebuked the heathen, thou hast destroyed the wicked, thou hast put out their name for ever and ever.
verses.verse_html: 5Thou hast rebuked the heathen, thou hast destroyed the wicked, thou hast put out their name for ever and ever.

verses.text_plain: O thou enemy, destructions are come to a perpetual end: and thou hast destroyed cities; their memorial is perished with them.
verses.verse_html:
6O thou enemy, destructions are come to a perpetual end: and thou hast destroyed cities; their memorial is perished with them. ▼
▼ O thou…: or, The destructions of the enemy are come to a perpetual end: and their cities hast thou destroyed, etc

footnotes.body_text: ▼ O thou…: or, The destructions of the enemy are come to a perpetual end: and their cities hast thou destroyed, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ O thou…: or, The destructions of the enemy are come to a perpetual end: and their cities hast thou destroyed, etc

verses.text_plain: But the Lord shall endure for ever: he hath prepared his throne for judgment.
verses.verse_html: 7But the Lord shall endure for ever: he hath prepared his throne for judgment.

verses.text_plain: And he shall judge the world in righteousness, he shall minister judgment to the people in uprightness.
verses.verse_html: 8And he shall judge the world in righteousness, he shall minister judgment to the people in uprightness.

verses.text_plain: The Lord also will be a refuge for the oppressed, a refuge in times of trouble.
verses.verse_html:
9The Lord also will be a refuge for the oppressed, a refuge in times of trouble. ▼
▼ a refuge: Heb. an high place

footnotes.body_text: ▼ a refuge: Heb. an high place
footnotes.body_html: ▼ a refuge: Heb. an high place

verses.text_plain: And they that know thy name will put their trust in thee: for thou, Lord, hast not forsaken them that seek thee.
verses.verse_html: 10And they that know thy name will put their trust in thee: for thou, Lord, hast not forsaken them that seek thee.

verses.text_plain: Sing praises to the Lord, which dwelleth in Zion: declare among the people his doings.
verses.verse_html: 11Sing praises to the Lord, which dwelleth in Zion: declare among the people his doings.

verses.text_plain: When he maketh inquisition for blood, he remembereth them: he forgetteth not the cry of the humble.
verses.verse_html:
12When he maketh inquisition for blood, he remembereth them: he forgetteth not the cry of the humble. ▼
▼ humble: or, afflicted

verses.text_plain: Have mercy upon me, O Lord; consider my trouble which I suffer of them that hate me, thou that liftest me up from the gates of death:
verses.verse_html: 13Have mercy upon me, O Lord; consider my trouble which I suffer of them that hate me, thou that liftest me up from the gates of death:

tokens.text: me, thou that liftest me up

verses.text_plain: That I may shew forth all thy praise in the gates of the daughter of Zion: I will rejoice in thy salvation.
verses.verse_html: 14That I may shew forth all thy praise in the gates of the daughter of Zion: I will rejoice in thy salvation.

verses.text_plain: The heathen are sunk down in the pit that they made: in the net which they hid is their own foot taken.
verses.verse_html: 15The heathen are sunk down in the pit that they made: in the net which they hid is their own foot taken.

verses.text_plain: The Lord is known by the judgment which he executeth: the wicked is snared in the work of his own hands. Higgaion. Selah.
verses.verse_html:
16The Lord is known by the judgment which he executeth: the wicked is snared in the work of his own hands. Higgaion. Selah. ▼
▼ Higgaion: that is, Meditation

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Higgaion: that is, Meditation

verses.text_plain: The wicked shall be turned into hell, and all the nations that forget God.
verses.verse_html: 17The wicked shall be turned into hell, and all the nations that forget God.

verses.text_plain: For the needy shall not alway be forgotten: the expectation of the poor shall not perish for ever.
verses.verse_html: 18For the needy shall not alway be forgotten: the expectation of the poor shall not perish for ever.

verses.text_plain: Arise, O Lord; let not man prevail: let the heathen be judged in thy sight.
verses.verse_html: 19Arise, O Lord; let not man prevail: let the heathen be judged in thy sight.

verses.text_plain: Put them in fear, O Lord: that the nations may know themselves to be but men. Selah.
verses.verse_html: 20Put them in fear, O Lord: that the nations may know themselves to be but men. Selah.
